Htmls:
The websites are located on the storage so you can use this application offline.

Instalation:
To run the program you have to install python 3 (or newer versions) and PyQt5.

Windows -

1. Installing python
	1. Go to python.org/downloads/
	2. Download python for Windows
	3. Run The instalation program
	
2. Installing PyQt5
	1. pip install PyQt5
Linux -

1. Installing python
	1. Open Terminal
	2. $ sudo apt-get install software-properties-common
	3. $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
	4. $ sudo apt-get update
	5. $ sudo apt-get install python3.8
	
2. Installing PyQt5
	1. $ sudo apt update && sudo apt install python3-pip
	2. $ pip3 install PyQt5
	3. $ sudo apt install qtcreator pyqt5-dev-tools

Utilization:

1. Open a console window in the Problem Solver '(Version 1.0 Beta)' folder.
2. $ python3 main.py

